** Shares of AI product-focused company Gorilla Technology Group GRRR slump 22.1% to $32.74, set for worst day in nearly two months 

** Blogger Edwin Dorsey, who runs the Bear Cave substack newsletter, releases negative research report on company 

** Dorsey says retail investor enthusiasm for GRRR is "premature" and "exact details of Gorilla's business and partnerships are a little fuzzy" 

** Company did not immediately respond to Reuters' request for comment 

** Both of the brokerages covering GRRR stock have a buy rating; their median PT is $31 - data compiled by LSEG

** GRRR shares have soared ~78% this year 

